	<p>
		Beevish Hospital’s Geriatric Department specializes in the unique healthcare needs of elderly patients, providing compassionate and comprehensive care. This department is dedicated to managing age-related conditions and enhancing the quality of life for older adults. With a team of experienced geriatricians, the department offers a wide range of services, from preventive screenings to chronic disease management.<br><br>

		The Geriatric team prioritizes individualized care, focusing on each patient’s medical history and personal needs. The department addresses common geriatric concerns such as mobility issues, memory loss, and chronic pain. Physicians work closely with patients and their families to ensure the best possible care, taking into account the physical, emotional, and social aspects of aging.<br><br>

		Preventive care is a cornerstone of the Geriatric Department’s approach. Regular screenings for conditions like osteoporosis, heart disease, and cognitive decline help detect issues early and improve patient outcomes. The department also provides vaccination programs and wellness advice to prevent illness and promote active, healthy aging.<br><br>

		Beevish Hospital’s Geriatric Department places a strong emphasis on rehabilitation, offering physical therapy and occupational therapy services to support independence. The team helps patients manage mobility challenges, aiming to prevent falls and injuries, which are common among elderly patients.<br><br>

		Education and support are essential components of geriatric care at Beevish. The department offers resources and counseling for patients and caregivers, helping them understand age-related health issues and make informed decisions. The team’s holistic approach ensures that elderly patients receive respectful, dignified care.
